Package net.cloud.server.event.task.voidtasks

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    VoidTask
    A VoidTask is some task which has no return value (void type) This is different from Task so that "return null" does not have to be included at the end of every execute method - easier lambda usage.
    Also contains default methods which take in the method used to schedule the task.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CancellableVoidTask
    A VoidTask which can be cancelled (via the task itself).
    ConnectTimeoutTask
    A task which will check to see if a player is still in the connected stage, and abort the connection if they are.
    CountedVoidTask
    A Task which will only execute a certain number of times (at least once).
    ErrorLoggingVoidTask
    A Task which will catch any errors from its execution and log them.
